#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn6.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The Appeal "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn6.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Brahmadevasutta "
msgstr "3. With Brahmadeva "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn6.3:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn6.3:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.3:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarissā brāhmaṇiyā brahmadevo nāma putto bhagavato santike agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time a certain brahmin lady had a son called Brahmadeva, who had gone forth from the lay life to homelessness in the presence of the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn6.3:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā brahmadevo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Brahmadeva, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.3:2.2"
msgid "“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi. "
msgstr "He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "

msgctxt "sn6.3:2.3"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā brahmadevo arahataṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "And Venerable Brahmadeva became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.141, pts2ed1.308, sc3
msgctxt "sn6.3:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā brahmadevo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then Brahmadeva robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.2"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena sakamātu nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Wandering indiscriminately for alms-food in Sāvatthī, he approached his own mother’s house. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.3:3.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato brahmadevassa mātā brāhmaṇī brahmuno āhutiṃ niccaṃ paggaṇhāti. "
msgstr "Now at that time Brahmadeva’s mother, the brahmin lady, was offering up a regular oblation to Brahmā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.3:3.4"
msgid "Atha kho brahmuno sahampatissa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati thought, "

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.5"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho āyasmato brahmadevassa mātā brāhmaṇī brahmuno āhutiṃ niccaṃ paggaṇhāti. "
msgstr "“This Venerable Brahmadeva’s mother, the brahmin lady, offers up a regular oblation to Brahmā. "

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ taṃ upasaṅkamitvā saṃvejeyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go and stir up a sense of urgency in her?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.3:3.7"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito āyasmato brahmadevassa mātu nivesane pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in the house of Brahmadeva’s mother. "

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.8"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati vehāsaṃ ṭhito āyasmato brahmadevassa mātaraṃ brāhmaṇiṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati, while standing in the air, addressed Brahmadeva’s mother in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.1"
msgid "“Dūre ito brāhmaṇi brahmaloko, "
msgstr "“Far from here is the Brahmā realm, madam, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.2"
msgid "Yassāhutiṃ paggaṇhāsi niccaṃ; "
msgstr "to which you offer a regular oblation. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.3"
msgid "Netādiso brāhmaṇi brahmabhakkho, "
msgstr "But Brahmā doesn’t eat that kind of food. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ajānaṃ → ajānantī (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.4"
msgid "Kiṃ jappasi brahmapathaṃ ajānaṃ. "
msgstr "Why make invocations, when you don’t know the path to Brahmā? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.1"
msgid "Eso hi te brāhmaṇi brahmadevo, "
msgstr "This Brahmadeva, madam, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.2"
msgid "Nirūpadhiko atidevapatto; "
msgstr "free of attachments, has surpassed the gods. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.3"
msgid "Akiñcano bhikkhu anaññaposī, "
msgstr "A mendicant without possessions or dependents, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: so → te so (pts1) | yo te sa (?)
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.4"
msgid "Yo te so piṇḍāya gharaṃ paviṭṭho. "
msgstr "he has entered your house for alms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.309, sc6
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.1"
msgid "Āhuneyyo vedagu bhāvitatto, "
msgstr "He’s worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, a knowledge master, self-developed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.2"
msgid "Narānaṃ devānañca dakkhiṇeyyo; "
msgstr "He’s worthy of a religious donation from gods and men. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.3"
msgid "Bāhitvā pāpāni anūpalitto, "
msgstr "Having shunned all evils, he’s unsullied. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.4"
msgid "Ghāsesanaṃ iriyati sītibhūto. "
msgstr "Cool at heart, he wanders looking for food. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.1"
msgid "Na tassa pacchā na puratthamatthi, "
msgstr "He has no before and after, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.2"
msgid "Santo vidhūmo anigho nirāso; "
msgstr "peaceful, unclouded, untroubled, with no need for hope, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.3"
msgid "Nikkhittadaṇḍo tasathāvaresu, "
msgstr "he has laid down the rod for all creatures firm and frail. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.4"
msgid "So tyāhutiṃ bhuñjatu aggapiṇḍaṃ. "
msgstr "So let him enjoy your offering of choice alms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.1"
msgid "Visenibhūto upasantacitto, "
msgstr "With peaceful mind, he has left the crowd, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.2"
msgid "Nāgova danto carati anejo; "
msgstr "he wanders like a tamed elephant, unperturbed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.3"
msgid "Bhikkhu susīlo suvimuttacitto, "
msgstr "He’s a mendicant fair in ethics, with heart well freed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.4"
msgid "So tyāhutiṃ bhuñjatu aggapiṇḍaṃ. "
msgstr "So let him enjoy your offering of choice alms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.142, sc9
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.1"
msgid "Tasmiṃ pasannā avikampamānā, "
msgstr "With unwavering confidence in him, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.2"
msgid "Patiṭṭhapehi dakkhiṇaṃ dakkhiṇeyye; "
msgstr "present your religious donation to one who is worthy of it. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.3"
msgid "Karohi puññaṃ sukhamāyatikaṃ, "
msgstr "Now that you’ve seen the sage who has crossed over, madam, "

# NOTE: This obviously represents the end of Brahma’s speech. What follows is according to the commentaries added by redactors.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.4"
msgid "Disvā muniṃ brāhmaṇi oghatiṇṇanti. "
msgstr "make merit for the sake of future happiness!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.310, sc10
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.1"
msgid "Tasmiṃ pasannā avikampamānā, "
msgstr "With unwavering confidence in him, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.2"
msgid "Patiṭṭhapesi dakkhiṇaṃ dakkhiṇeyye; "
msgstr "she presented her religious donation to one who is worthy of it. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.3"
msgid "Akāsi puññaṃ sukhamāyatikaṃ, "
msgstr "After seeing the sage who had crossed over, the brahmin lady "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.4"
msgid "Disvā muniṃ brāhmaṇī oghatiṇṇan”ti. "
msgstr "made merit for the sake of future happiness."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
